The abducted chairman of the Independent Petroleum Marketers Association of Nigeria (IPMAN), Benin Depot, Alhaji Abdul-Hamid Egele, has finally regained regained freedom from his abductors. Popularly called Baba Petrol, the IPMAN chairman was kidnapped 7 February, at the gate of his house in Jattu, Etsako West local government area of Edo State. According to a family source Thursday evening, Egele was released after N70 million was paid as ransom in far away Kaduna State. According to the family source: “He was released yesterday morning after a ransom of N70 million was paid in Kaduna. “As we speak, he is in an undisclosed hospital in Benin receiving treatment.” The abductors had earlier demanded for N80 million for his freedom. Edo Police Command spokesman, SP Kontongs Bello, could not be reached for a reaction. Abuja - Governments and relations of kidnap victims may have paid over N20billion as ransom in various parts of the country in the last two years. Information gleaned from an Intelligence Tracking Company in Nigeria also revealed that no part of the country was spared by the activities of the… In "Top Stories" From Jude Owuamanam, Managing Editor,  Northern Operations JOS (Sundiata Post) - Sundiata Post can confirm that kidnapped chairman of the Peoples Democratic Party in Plateau State,  Mr. Damishi Sango; his son;  Plateau State coordinator of Prince Uche Secondus Campaign Organisation, Chief Emmanuel Magni,  and two others who were abducted last… In "News" By Peter Amine Jos -  Sheikh Abdulazeez Yusuf, the 90-year-old Administrative Secretary of Plateau chapter of the Jama’atu Nasirul Islam, who was kidnapped on Wednesday, has been released, according to JNI spokesman, Sani Mudi. “The cleric has regained his freedom alongside his driver,” Mudi told the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN)… In "News"